body.p:
Two projects began in the first decade of the century to fund researchers to make collections of documentary materials. One was based at the Max Planck Institute for Psycholinguistics (Nijmegen, The Netherlands) and funded by the Volkswagen Stiftung;
                 Dokumentation Bedrohte Sprache (DoBeS): http://dobes.mpi.nl/ the other was based at the School of Oriental and African Studies (London, UK), funded by Arcadia.
                 Hans Rausing Endangered Languages Project: http://www.hrelp.org MPI Nijmegen had a well-resourced technical department which took responsibility for developing the archiving stream of the DoBeS project. HRELP had to build their archive from scratch; no existing resources at SOAS were available to support their work. For both projects, it was a requirement of funded research that data were deposited in the relevant archive. Both archives, however, are open to deposits from non-funded researchers.
